                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Andrew, the presbyter and
                            archimandrite of the holy cloisters of <span class="tei-placeName"> Caria </span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3134-6" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Andrew</span> was male.  <a href="/3134-7" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName"> Andrew
                                </span> was a presbyter.  <a href="/3134-8" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName"> Andrew
                                </span> was a archimandrite.  <a href="/3134-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">
                            Photius and 
                            Andrew were fellow monastics. <a href="/3134-10" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Andrew and
                                Photius
                            was a monastic authority over Anonymous 3730. <a href="/3134-14" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Severus of
                                Antioch sent a letter to Photius and 
                            Andrew. <a href="/3134-5" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">
                            Sometime between 519 and 525
                            Severus of Antioch anwered a letter he received from 
                            Photius and 
                            Andrew on the subject of receiving
                            clergy from Nestorian and Diphysite groups who renounce their heresy and make a right confession and on 
                            whether or not catechumens, the demon possed, and penitents should be present for the Lord's Supper.
                            Severus of Antioch states that after a period 
                            of repentance they should  be received into the same rank without re-baptism or re-ordination.
                         <a href="/3134-43" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
